\begin_layout Section
Concept of force
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A stone falls to the ground, a cricket ball crosses boundary, a swimmer
 plunges into a swimming pool.
 What causes the movement in each of these cases? In each of these examples
 the motion is caused by a push or pull.
 We use the word 
\series bold
force
\series default
 to describe pushes and pulls.
 In all the examples above force has 
\series bold
changed the speed
\series default
 of an object.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A force may change
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
